title: Ali Amin Khan wins NA-44 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Ali Amin Khan has won the election for the National Assembly constituency from NA-44 Dera Ismail Khan-I by securing 93,443 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat-e-Ulema Islam Pakistan candidate Fazal Ur Rehman, who bagged 59,922 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 55.51 percent.
